[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has a minimum 1\S opening bid - 13 points and five trumps. She doesn't even suspect 
what's about to befall!

NORTH hears the 1\S bid and all he wants to know is whether SOUTH has one, two or three Aces. 
So he uses the Blackwood convention, 4NT.

SOUTH has two Aces so she bids 5\H (5\C would show zero Aces, 
5\D would show one Ace, etc).

NORTH has heard enough and bids 6\S.}

