[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has an above-minimum strength hand with a good 6-card suit. He opens 1\H.

NORTH, with 9 points, is a little too weak to bid at the 2-level so she bids a catchall 1NT.

SOUTH shows his 6-card suit and extra strength by jumping to 3\H, which 
NORTH raises to 4\H since two trumps is now adequate support.}

